&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title and Grade:&lt;/strong&gt; Band 5 Pharmacy Technician (Accredited Checking Technician)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location/Trust:&lt;/strong&gt; Rotherham General Hospital, Moorgate Road, Rotherham, S60 2UD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department Covered:&lt;/strong&gt; Pharmacy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rates:  &lt;/strong&gt;£15.60&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Placement Ref/ID&lt;/strong&gt;: 36537 &amp; 36538&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:        &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A passion for putting patients first&lt;/strong&gt; …… join the bank for flexibility in how you work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of a Trust who are committed to empowering their clinicians and managers to deliver real benefits to patients and their carers, that has developed a reputation as a thriving and successful organisation?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you answered ‘yes’ to the above, we’d love to hear from you! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have long term placement opportunities available for Medicine Management Technicians available at The Rotherham NHS Foundation Trust, specifically providing the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Job Purpose:   To carry out appropriate technical duties within the pharmacy department, working in close liaison with pharmacy, medical and nursing staff and other health care professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Holds accreditation for the accuracy checking of dispensed prescriptions by members of staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsible for the day to day workflow and supervision of Pharmacy Technicians, Assistant Technical Officers and pharmacy support workers working in the dispensary, and rotational Pre- Registration Pharmacist and Pre- Registration Pharmacy Technicians.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Key Result Areas and Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To provide evidence of and maintain registration as a practicing Pharmacy Technician with the General Pharmaceutical Council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To assess and interpret prescription documentation in order to then dispense&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;inpatient, outpatient, discharge medication and clinical trial prescriptions with a high degree of accuracy in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To deal with face to face and telephone requests and queries whilst undertaking reception duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To counsel patients when providing medicines using information leaflets and verbal information on common pharmaceutical issues under the supervision of the responsible pharmacist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use appropriate computer programmes to dispense prescriptions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To assess and interpret prescription documentation with a high degree of accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To dispense controlled drugs in line with regulations, ensuring records and stock are maintained correctly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To undertake the duties of an accredited accuracy checker:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check prescriptions,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide supervision for Pharmacy Technicians, Pre- Registration Pharmacists or Pharmacists participating in accuracy checking training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage the work flow and request additional help if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BTEC and NVQ level 3 in pharmaceutical science services or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered as a Pharmacy Technician with GPhC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accredited accuracy checking (ACT) qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desirable Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working knowledge of JAC, Microsoft Office, Pharmacy labelling systems, Meditech, Sepia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates &lt;/strong&gt;- work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of placements at over 50 NHS Trusts in England&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dedicated consultants&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working options&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free DBS and free training&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days – &lt;/strong&gt;Call us anytime on 03330 144 370&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who are NHS Professionals?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Professionals (NHSP), owned by the Department of Health and Social Care (DHSC), works in partnership with hospital trusts to provide a bank of highly skilled temporary workers who want to work flexibly within the NHS. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through the NHSP bank means Trusts don’t have to rely on expensive agencies. Right now, we have over 130,000 members registered on our bank from various roles, grades and specialities, saving the NHS over &lt;strong&gt;£70 million&lt;/strong&gt; each year. This money is then reinvested back into the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Register today for various flexible working options and long-term placement opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on the roles or details on how to join NHS Professionals, simply get in touch with Phil Chafer, Recruitment &amp; Placement Consultant on 01442915242 or &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Philip.chafer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclaimer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion&lt;/p&gt;
